OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1780927877
OL,3,CHow innocent man was jailed and the
OL,4,Creal rapist went free
OL,6,FQuinn, 52, evaded justice for more
OL,7,Fthan two decades but was found guilty
OL,8,Fof two counts of rape, one count of
OL,9,Fchoking with intent and one count of
OL,10,Fgrievous bodily harm after DNA
OL,11,Ftechnology linked him to the crime.
OL,13,FBut how did it happen?
OL,15,F19 July 2003
OL,17,FA young mother in her 30s is brutally
OL,18,Fattacked and raped, walking home in
OL,19,Fthe early hours of the morning on
OL,20,FCleggs Lane, Little Hulton, Salford.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,400,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1780927877
OL,3,CHow innocent man was jailed and the
OL,4,Creal rapist went free
OL,6,FHours later two local police officers
OL,7,Fidentify Mr Malkinson, a security
OL,8,Fguard at a local shopping centre, as a
OL,9,Fpotential suspect.
OL,11,FShe told police she had clawed at her
OL,12,Fattacker's face, snapping a nail and
OL,13,Fleaving a deep scratch.
OL,15,FBut when Mr Malkinson was arrested he
OL,16,Fhad no such scratch and vehemently
OL,17,Fprotested his innocence.
OL,19,F3 August 2003
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
