PN,39905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1780927877
OL,3,CHow innocent man was jailed and the
OL,4,Creal rapist went free
OL,6,FAt his trial, the victim said she had
OL,7,Fdoubts about her identification of Mr
OL,8,FMalkinson, but was reassured by
OL,9,Fdetectives her wavering was just
OL,10,F"trial nerves".
OL,12,FNo DNA could be found linking Mr
OL,13,FMalkinson to the crime and the
OL,14,Fprosecution relied on the
OL,15,Fidentification evidence of three
OL,16,Fwitnesses.
OL,18,FMr Malkinson appeals against his
OL,19,Fconviction and sentence for the first
OL,20,Ftime, but it is dismissed by the Court
OL,21,Fof Appeal.
OL,26,@rD@AOUrD@NO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
